free: #e In the past, Hanako's husband was in Spukunu.
#e In the war, people there also followed (to fight).
#c 以前戰爭的時候，那邊的人也有跟著去(打仗)
#n 表面字意為摔角打鬥，但在此指以前戰爭的時候。
#e Every time I went there, he definitely told (such a story).
#c 我每次去那邊他每次必定都講(這件事)。
#e For example, they had been considering to ask for money from Japan.
#c 比方說， 他們曾經曾經想要向日本要錢。
#n '他們'指那時去南洋參加戰爭的人。
#e Yes. If.... How should we say...?
#c 對. 如果說... 該怎麼說....?
#n 這裡的si 應該是講成有la比較好，如：la-si [HAB-3SG]
#e It is heard that they gave some.
#e Perhaps they complained the money insufficient, so they still keep on exercising.
#c 不曉得他們到底是不是嫌不夠，他們還在不斷的運動當中。
#e In the beginning, when XXX had not been proposed, (people there) also stood out for the activity of asking for (the compensation money).
#c 最初, 還沒有說XXX,...曾經 剛開始的時候, （那邊的人）也出來參加討錢的活動。
#e (They) may possibly consider it is not enough.
#e For those dead, they gave (the money) indeed.
#e My real grandfathers, they are all....
#c 我的爺爺，他們已經全部。
#e My father also brought (the money) to my aunt and grandmother.
#c 我的爸爸也有拿去給我的姑姑和祖母。
#n ino-coni 為 "姑姑/阿姨" 之親屬稱謂語。
#e Salary, yes, (he got) salary when he was a solider.
#c 薪水，對，他是拿那時當兵的薪水。
#e Not so much, there was only 75,000 Japanese Yens for 3 years.
#c 那沒有很多啦，三年才七萬五千元。
#e (That money) was somewhat able to pacify (you).
#c 還算是有稍微安撫的意思。
#e (The money/The Japanese government had to somewhat pacify (you) at least.
#e Weren't you almost killed by western people?
#c 你不是差一點被洋人幹掉啊？
#e In a war, by nature no one really takes advantage.
#c 戰爭原本就沒有人真正佔到便宜。
#e Grandfather, have you ever said that, if you had really failed, you would almost have been killed by the Americans?
#c Ak'i (外公)你不是有講過說，如果說你們失敗的話，你們幾乎要被美國人幹掉了？
#e If we had kept lingering there, Japanese would have been beaten within one month.
#c 如果我們一直逗留在那邊，不到一個月日本人已經被打敗了。
#e If the Japanese were not defeated at that time, the war would have not yet finished.
#c 如果那個時候還沒有把日本人打敗的話，戰爭還沒有結束。
#e Yes, (at that time) Japanese had been knocked down.
#c 對啊，那時候已經把日本人扳倒了。
#c 讓你們回家嗎？（是不是就這樣子給你們回家？）
#e Didn't you deliberately intend to lose?
#c 你們是不是原本就存心失敗？
#n speaker's slip of tongue. tiate should be niate 'almost'.
#e Especially, Japanese joined force and continuously invaded (other countries).
#c 特別是,日本人合力一直侵略(別人)。
#e (Japanese) wanted to invade (the areas) Korea, the other side of the Taiwan Strait, Taiwan and Nanyang.
#c (日本人) 想要侵略從朝鮮到對岸，台灣，到南洋。
#e Cou people at that time should be highly respected.
#e Not only we Tsou, but there were also a lot of aborignes from other places.
#c 不僅只是我們鄒人，別的地方的原住民應該也有很多。
#e At least all the aborigines in Taiwan.
#c 反正就是全台灣的原住民。
#c 全部自己不用在一直seising... seisicu。
